The Layeni and Pako police stations in Ifelodun and, Apapa- Iganmu LCDA were on Tuesday afternoon set ablaze by hoodlums under the guise of the #EndSARS protests. The incident bring to three police stations burnt down in Lagos as at Tuesday afternoon. The Nation had reported the Orile police station was set ablaze by hoodlums in the morning. Responding to the burning down of the Orile police station and the violent dimension the protest had assumed, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu declared a 24-hour curfew in the state. The other two police stations were said to have been set ablaze few hours after the announcement of the curfew, raising speculation that it might have been in reaction to the declaration of curfew. Details shortlyâ€¦